    "en": {
      "title": "The case against Cabral is adjourned until November",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Fort Magistrate Thilina Gamage has adjourned the case until November (11th) next month to submit an amended complaint against the former Central Bank Governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Cabral regarding an alleged misappropriation of US$ 65 million belonging to the Government of Sri Lanka. Ordered today (23).",
        "Former Central Bank Governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Cabral appeared in court today (23) on bail in connection with this incident.",
        "President's lawyer Mr. Sampath Mendis, who appeared in court on behalf of former Central Bank governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Cabral, stated that he hopes to file preliminary objections related to this incident.",
        "Nugegoda Nalandaramadhipati Thiniawala Palitha Thero has submitted a complaint related to this incident.",
        "In his complaint, the complainant submitted that in the year 2014, an amount of US$ 6.5 million belonging to the Central Bank of Sri Lanka was paid to Ahmed Sbriri, who was working for the American CIA spy service, under the guise of improving the image of Sri Lanka. has been ."
